1. **Core Design Flaw (HIGH/TP)**: `SafeHtmlValidator.isValid()` uses `Cleaner.isValid()` (boolean check) instead of `Cleaner.clean()` (sanitization). The original unsanitized HTML string is stored/used by the application even when validation passes, meaning any XSS payload that passes whitelist validation is stored as-is.

2. **RELAXED Default Whitelist (HIGH/TP)**: The `@SafeHtml` annotation defaults to `RELAXED` whitelist (broadest allowed set of HTML tags including div, img, table, etc.) and the validator at line 49 applies this permissive whitelist.

